      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "No. Telehealth psychology — delivered via video — is available from any registered psychologist in NSW, regardless of where they are based. The Medicare rebate is identical for telehealth and in-person sessions (from 1 July 2025: $145.25 with an endorsed clinical psychologist; $98.95 with a registered psychologist). Whether you live in Bondi Junction, Randwick, Coogee, Rose Bay, or Vaucluse, you can access a practitioner based anywhere in NSW via telehealth. That said, our directory does include practitioners with practices in Bondi Junction and Edgecliff who may also offer in-person appointments."
