      "name": "Is telehealth psychology effective for anxiety?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, for most people. A 2023 systematic review published in JMIR Mental Health (Shaker et al.) found that telehealth CBT produced outcomes for anxiety disorders comparable to in-person delivery across multiple measures including anxiety symptom severity and quality of life. The therapeutic techniques that make CBT and ACT effective — structured exposure, cognitive restructuring, behavioural activation, skills practice — translate fully to a video session. Some people prefer in-person for reasons of comfort or specific clinical need; that option is also available from eastern suburbs practitioners."
      }
